Timeline of Mutex Lock in Action:

T=0ms    1000 users hit GET /matches/1 simultaneously
         (Cache is cold/expired)
         
T=1ms    User #1: SET lock:match:1 'locked' NX
         ✅ Returns 'OK' - Lock acquired!
         
         Users #2-1000: SET lock:match:1 'locked' NX
         ❌ Returns null - Lock already exists
         → They wait 50ms and retry
         
T=2ms    User #1: Queries database (SELECT * FROM matches WHERE id=1)
         (Database processes the ONE query)
         
T=50ms   User #1: Gets result from DB
         User #1: Updates cache (SETs match:1 in Redis)
         User #1: Deletes lock (DELs lock:match:1)
         ✅ Lock released!
         
         Users #2-1000: Retry their SET lock (50ms passed)
         ❌ Lock is gone but cache now exists!
         → CACHE HIT! Return immediately
         
Result: Database got hit ONCE instead of 1000 times! 🎯